headline: Why Centene (CNC) Stock Is Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of health coverage company Centene (NYSE:CNC) fell 3.3% in the morning session after JPMorgan cut its price target on the managed care company to $30 from $48. This move by JPMorgan followed Centene's recent second-quarter earnings report, where the company posted a loss of $0.16 per share, missing analyst estimates.
